{"id":439,"category_slug":"english-conversations","category_name":"Conversations","position":41,"title":"41. Oral Exams","subtitle":"","level":"B1","parts":26,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/english-conversations/41-oral-exams.439/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/0-41-oral-exams.mp3","transcript":"Hey, Cindy! Have you finished the exam?\nYes, I have. Whew!\nWas it hard?\nWell, yes. It was hard, pretty hard.\nDid you pass?\nI don't know. Mrs. Lester didn't tell me.\nWhat questions did she ask?\nFirst she asked me what my name was.\nThat was easy, wasn't it?\nYes, except I couldn't remember!\nThen she asked me where I came from,\nand how long it took to get here from my country.\nAnd what else did she ask?\nShe asked how long I'd been studying English here in Canada,\nand she asked how I would use English in the future.\nYes, yes, go on.\nThen she asked me to explain the difference between my country and Canada.\nAnything else?\nI'm trying to remember.\nOh, yes! She asked if I spoke any other language.\nIs that all?\nOh, there were a lot of other questions. She asked me what my hobbies were,\nwhere I visited in Canada. Then I was asked to read a passage.\nWhat did she say at the end?\nHmm. Let's see...\nOh, Yes! She asked me to tell you to go in, right away.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:48:43","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Hey, Cindy! Have you finished the exam?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/1.mp3","time_start":2.25,"time_end":4.27},{"position":2,"content":"Yes, I have. Whew!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/2.mp3","time_start":4.27,"time_end":5.93},{"position":3,"content":"Was it hard?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/3.mp3","time_start":5.98,"time_end":6.96},{"position":4,"content":"Well, yes. It was hard, pretty hard.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/4.mp3","time_start":6.96,"time_end":8.86},{"position":5,"content":"Did you pass?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/5.mp3","time_start":8.86,"time_end":9.64},{"position":6,"content":"I don't know. Mrs. Lester didn't tell me.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/6.mp3","time_start":9.68,"time_end":11.8},{"position":7,"content":"What questions did she ask?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/7.mp3","time_start":11.87,"time_end":13.38},{"position":8,"content":"First she asked me what my name was.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/8.mp3","time_start":13.38,"time_end":15.12},{"position":9,"content":"That was easy, wasn't it?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/9.mp3","time_start":15.12,"time_end":16.38},{"position":10,"content":"Yes, except I couldn't remember!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/10.mp3","time_start":16.38,"time_end":18.08},{"position":11,"content":"Then she asked me where I came from,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/11.mp3","time_start":18.08,"time_end":19.72},{"position":12,"content":"and how long it took to get here from my country.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/41-oral-exams-2022-03-07-21-18-39/12.mp3","time_start":19.72,"time_end":22.16},{"position":13,"content":"And what else did she ask?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/uploa